    <header>
      <span class="badge">SN Code Analyzer</span>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: September 6, 2025</p>
    </header>

    <div class="card">
      <h2>1) Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how the <strong>SN Code Analyzer</strong> extension handles data when you install and use it in your browser.
        We value your privacy and are committed to protecting it.
      </p>

      <h2>2) Scope</h2>
      <p>
        This policy applies solely to the SN Code Analyzer extension and not to any third-party websites or services
        you may access through your browser.
      </p>

      <h2>3) Data Collection</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>SN Code Analyzer does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.</strong>
        Code analysis (e.g., scripts, tags, snippets) happens <em>locally</em> in your browser. No information
        from your pages or ServiceNow environment is sent to external servers by the extension.
      </p>
      <p class="muted">
        Note: if you manually enable optional features (e.g., sending a report via email or export),
        such data is handled by the chosen service (email client, export tool) and does not pass through our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>4) Browser Permissions</h2>
      <p>
        The extension may request certain <em>Chrome permissions</em> strictly required for its operation (e.g., <code>scripting</code>, <code>activeTab</code>, <code>storage</code>).
        These permissions are used only to analyze the code of the active tab at your request, display results, and
        store your preferences <em>locally</em> (in <code>chrome.storage</code>).
      </p>

      <h2>5) Use and Retention</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No profiling, no targeted advertising, no selling of data.</li>
        <li>Analysis results and settings remain on your device until you delete them (via the UI or by uninstalling the extension).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>6) Sharing and Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        We do not share, rent, or sell any user data to third parties. No transfer outside of your device is performed by the extension.
      </p>

      <h2>7) Security</h2>
      <p>
        Local execution reduces risks. We follow best practices for extension development (least privilege, permission reviews, local storage) to minimize the attack surface.
      </p>

      <h2>8) Children</h2>
      <p>
        The extension is not intended for children under 13 and does not process any data that could identify them.
      </p>

      <h2>9) Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy if features evolve. The “Last updated” date will be adjusted accordingly. In case of major changes, we will notify users on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>10) Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        For any questions, contact us at: <a href="mailto:contact@example.com">contact@example.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

